&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;McAdams is a full-service land planning, landscape architecture, civil engineering, transportation, and geomatics firm located in North Carolina, South Carolina, Texas, and Florida. We seek to partner with our clients to create meaningful experiences through inspired design. Our employees are what make McAdams different. We bring experiences to the forefront of everything we do, and to do that takes special people.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Client Development Manager, you will help lead business development in Charlotte by building strong client relationships, generating a healthy pipeline of opportunities, and supporting the continued growth of the firm. We are looking for a resourceful, passionate, and dedicated professional who takes initiative, works well across teams, and is motivated by helping a growth-oriented firm win new work. In this client-facing role, you will collaborate with operational, marketing, and leadership teams to actively contribute to metro revenue growth by generating qualified opportunities, advancing pursuits, and helping convert relationships into awarded work. This role will also provide occasional support to nearby offices (e.g., Asheville, Greenville, and Winston-Salem), including periodic travel to strengthen regional relationships and coordination.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relationship Development ‐ Build and maintain relationships with existing and prospective clients, industry partners, and decision-makers in Charlotte with a focus on identifying, shaping, and advancing opportunities into the active proposal pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct client meetings, local outreach, and presentations that position McAdams’ brand, capabilities, and differentiators in the market with the goal of identifying upcoming needs, influencing project opportunities early, and positioning McAdams for future pursuits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the firm in local and regional events, associations, and networking forums with the goal of uncovering qualified leads, strengthening target account access, and expanding the project pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in leadership roles within industry-specific professional organizations and use those connections to create qualified opportunities, strengthen strategic relationships, and support proposal and revenue growth&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Leadership &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement a targeted business development strategy for Charlotte metro that is designed to create proposal opportunities, expand pipeline, and contribute to metro revenue goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with local leaders to identify, qualify, prioritize, and actively advance pursuits ensuring consistent movement of opportunities into proposals and awarded work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct market research and analyze local trends to identify emerging opportunities, strategic accounts, and priority sectors in Charlotte metro.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support firmwide market sector efforts in designated strategic areas by coordinating local intelligence, relationships, and pursuit activity with enterprise priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Leadership and Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with marketing, operational teams, and metro leadership to identify, position, and win new project opportunities, taking an active role in driving pursuit strategy, pre-positioning, and go/no-go alignment.&lt;/li&gt;
